#MUDPROG
Progtype  speech_prog~
Arglist   p look?~
Comlist   sayto $n You don't look like much of anything, yet! Books are what people+
remember, and believe me, $n, I'm the premier author around here. Now, you+
and I know what you look like in reality. It's our little secret! But how+
you want people to see you in Njata is important.
mpsleep 10
sayto $n You see, regardless of what you really look like-- you know what I+
mean! -- the way you're perceived in Njata is important. You wouldn't want+
anyone to suspect you aren't from this world, now, would you?"
mpsleep 10
sayto $n To start, tell me about your eyes, and your hair or horns or+
whatever it is you have on your head. Go on, try it. For example, I have+
[eyes] flint-dark eyes, and [hair] white, thin hair pulled back into a+
ponytail."
mpsleep 10
sayto $n When you're done, you let me know.
~
#ENDPROG

