#ROOM
Vnum     200
Name     Small and Simple Room~
Sector   city~
Flags    nomob safe prototype~
Desc     This small and simple room appears to be the study of an industrious
recordskeeper. All four walls are taken up by sturdy oaken [bookshelves],
filled to bursting with leatherbound books and loose sheaves of paper.
There are no apparent exits, and the light in the room seems to be coming
from a stained-glass [mosaic] window set in the ceiling. The center of the
room is taken up by a large, stone [table] with mysterious runes carved in
its surface.
~
Reset M 0 200 2 200
#EXDESC
ExDescKey    bookshelves~
ExDesc       These bookshelves are doublestacked and haphazardly piled with every sort
of tome one might imagine. Several books appear to be marked [History of
Njata], all with red spines. There is another set gilded with [gold], and
one especially large tome that has the name [Chieftain] scrawled along its
spine.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    mosaic~
ExDesc       Lit by a soft sunlight, as if it were the break of day, this mosaic depicts
a massive ship sailing upon dark waves, through a violent storm. It
appears to be captained by sphinxes and fairies. Circling the central
imagery are depictions of heroic figures of every race found in Njata.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    table~
ExDesc       Carved into the table are runes in the common tongue. They spell out the
names of four continents: Ajax, Lavada, Dori, and Colista. There is a
fifth, but it is faint and difficult to read.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#MUDPROG
Progtype  act_prog~
Arglist   p squints at the table.~
Comlist   mea $n Squinting at the table reveals that the last continent is Dogala.
~
#ENDPROG

